Text.Value: An ugly thought. With the echo of truth to it.
You've heard some of it, I'm sure. That I froze, or broke, or some other lie that is kinder than the truth.
As you wish. I'll pray for your success, to any god who will listen.
The Blade of Frontiers. The saviour I needed, if not the one I deserved.
Mind your own business, Zevlor.
I paid the price of angering the wrong devil.
I see...
The others. The ambush - tell me they survived.
Watching gods - the Blade of Frontiers? Wyll? What happened?
It would be nice to think so. But whatever these monsters twist us into... I believe it begins in us.
I won't make excuses. I can't make amends. But I know something of what you came to do - I want to help, if you'll let me.
Of course. Forgive me.
By the time I regained my senses, it was too late. I did not just surrender to the Absolute. For a moment, I welcomed it.
I... owe you an explanation. Much more than that. But first, please...
And all the while, the cult tortured them. They fought, and ran, and died around me, while I imagined myself their saviour.

EditorData.NodeContext: No heat or self-pity - just the clarity of his failure

Text.Value: I would be a paladin again - with a god's purpose, a god's power. Everything I needed to protect my people.
I fell short of that mark in Avernus - and even so, it was not so bad as this.
They did? Oh sweet gods. I have no right to feel it - but I am proud of them.
Fine. Good luck, Zevlor.
'For a moment' - until you realised your reward would be a tadpole.
The only survivors ended up in a cell in Moonrise.
Somehow, I suspect it's worse even than you imagine. Likely you heard that I broke, or froze, or some other lie kinder than the truth.
Ketheric is below. He thinks you're no longer a menace. Descend and show him how wrong he is.
Find your own people. They need you.
Hells... I didn't think I was going to make it. Thank you...
They're all dead.
Go, my friend. Please. Let me do this much.
And shouldered the cost to spare someone else a worse fate, I'd wager.
If there are any more survivors to be found, I'll find them - and lead them out of this place.
Gods... it's all my fault.
Your people didn't need a paladin - they saved themselves.
Some. Others ended up in a cell in Moonrise. That's on you.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: |Needs appropriate flag checks for various fates of Tieflings.|

Text.Value: I could use another blade in the fight to come.
I paid the price of angering the wrong devil.
Until I realised what I'd done. Perhaps I fought - I don't recall. Either way, I was deemed... unworthy of becoming a True Soul.
And shouldered the cost to spare someone else a worse fate, I'd wager.
*Confusion crosses Zevlor's eyes as he takes you in.*
Only if you can trust it won't be buried in your back. The Absolute swayed me once before. I won't risk it happening again.
I thought I was done for... Thank you... Watching gods - the Blade of Frontiers? Wyll? What happened?
Be honest. You wanted the power, but not for any ideal - for yourself.
I don't care what you do - just get out of my sight.
Finish what you came here to do - I daresay you've done enough for me.
I can't tell you.
You abandoned them. Do you really think you have the right to ask?
Zevlor.
I figured I was due a makeover. What do you think?
As for my sorry state...
If I know you at all, you chose this fate to spare someone else a worse one. So I think it suits you.
They found refuge. But what the hells happened out there, Zevlor?
And you, my friend. And pathetic, inadequate as it is - thank you.
It sounds like you were being enthralled. It's not your fault.
Some. No thanks to you.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: |Needs appropriate flag checks for various fates of Tieflings.|

Text.Value: They have you.
We were ambushed by cultists, yes. And then I heard... Her. Their false god, whispering promises in my mind.
If you wanted power, you never needed a god - only to live up to your ideal.
I do not. But if you know what happened... well, you deserve to know all of it.

Synopsis: Dialogue with Zevlor after freeing him from his pod in the Colony Tadpoling Centre.
